CBOT corn closes lower on sharp break in soybeans . A sharp drop in soybean futures plus overall good crop weather in the U . S . Midwest pressed CBOT corn futures to a lower close , traders said . Active speculative selling led the way down with several key managed fund accounts combining to sell roughly 18 million bushels of corn futures , traders said . The market also was pressed by aggressive corn seeding in the U . S . Midwest and by routine exports of U . S . corn , traders said . USDA Monday reported U . S . corn seedings as of Sunday at a level well above a year ago and above average and rapid corn plantings were expected this week , traders said . Thursday ' s USDA weekly export sales report was expected to show net U . S . corn sales at 300 , 000 to 600 , 000 tonnes . Merrill Lynch Futures sold 4 . 5 million bushels of July , Rosenthal Collins sold three million July and Cargill Inc sold 5 . 5 million bushels of July , traders said . Griffin Trading sold three million bushels of December and FIMAT Futures sold five million bushels of December , traders said . Corn closed 3 / 4 to 3 - 1 / 2 cents per bushel lower , with May down 3 - 1 / 2 at $ 2 . 85 - 3 / 4 . July was down one at $ 2 . 83 - 1 / 2 and December was down one at $ 2 . 65 - 3 / 4 . In spread trading , Lind Waldock did two million July / September at 15 - 3 / 4 cents , Goldenberg Hehmeyer did 1 . 5 million July / December at 19 cents and Refco Inc spread one million July / December at 18 - 1 / 2 cents , traders said . Corn futures volume was estimated by the CBOT at 65 , 000 contracts , below the 73 , 123 traded Tuesday . In corn options , Lind Waldock sold 1 , 100 July $ 2 . 90 puts at 12 to 12 - 1 / 2 cents , Cargill Investor Services bought 400 July $ 2 . 90 calls and bought 400 July $ 2 . 80 puts at 6 - 1 / 4 cents and Goldenberg Hehmeyer bought 200 July $ 3 . 40 calls at 5 / 8 cent , traders said . Corn options volume was estimated at 16 , 000 contracts , below the 17 , 502 traded Tuesday . ( ( Sam Nelson 312 - 408 - 8721 ) ) 
